(449, 45, 1, 3, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO3 (1.0) as providing safe and effective dental care in a holistic manner is a core problem-solving activity. It also maps strongly to PLO1 (0.8), PLO2 (0.8), and PLO4 (0.8).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(450, 45, 1, 4, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO4 (1.0) as it is explicitly about evidence-based practice and clinical decision-making, which includes research skills.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(451, 45, 2, 5, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO6 (0.8) as professionalism includes recognizing one\'s own limitations and continuously improving. It also maps moderately to PLO3 (0.5), PLO4 (0.5), and PLO5 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(452, 45, 2, 6, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO3 (0.8), PLO4 (0.8), and PLO6 (0.8) as clinical skills, evidence-based practice, and professionalism are the keys to adaptability in the dental field.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(453, 45, 2, 7, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO1 (0.8), PLO3 (0.8), and PLO4 (0.8) as scientific knowledge, clinical skills, and evidence-based practice all require adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(454, 45, 2, 8, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO4 (1.0) as evidence-based practice is central to lifelong learning.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(455, 45, 3, 9, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO2 (0.8) as disease prevention and population health require cultural awareness. It also maps moderately to PLO1 (0.5), PLO3 (0.5), PLO5 (0.5), and PLO6 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(456, 45, 3, 10, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO5 (1.0) as it is explicitly about communication skills.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(457, 45, 3, 11, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO2 (1.0) as disease prevention and population health require awareness of local and international issues. It also maps moderately to PLO3 (0.5), PLO4 (0.5), and PLO6 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(458, 45, 4, 12, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO6 (0.8) as professionalism in the local context requires an understanding of Arabic-Islamic identity and values. It also maps moderately to PLO5 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(459, 45, 4, 13, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO5 (0.8) and PLO6 (0.8) as communication and professionalism both require embracing diversity. It also maps moderately to PLO2 (0.5) and PLO3 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(460, 45, 4, 14, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO6 (1.0) as it is explicitly about professionalism and ethical guidelines.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(461, 45, 4, 15, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO2 (1.0) as disease prevention and population health are core aspects of civic engagement for a dentist. It also maps strongly to PLO6 (0.8).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(462, 45, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO3 (0.8) and PLO4 (0.8) as clinical skills and evidence-based practice drive innovation in dentistry. It also maps moderately to PLO1 (0.5) and PLO2 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(463, 45, 5, 18, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO3 (0.8) and PLO5 (0.8) as clinical skills and communication are essential for collaboration.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(464, 45, 5, 19, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO3 (0.8) as providing safe and effective dental care requires management skills. It also maps moderately to PLO2 (0.5) and PLO6 (0.5).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(465, 45, 5, 20, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO5 (1.0) as it is explicitly about interpersonal communication skills. It also maps strongly to PLO6 (0.8).', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(466, 45, 5, 21, 'This competency is most strongly mapped to PLO3 (0.8), PLO5 (0.8), and PLO6 (0.8) as clinical skills, communication, and professionalism all provide opportunities for leadership.', '', '2026-02-20 13:37:45', '2026-02-20 13:37:45'),
(467, 52, 1, 1, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO1, as it directly involves applying key theories and concepts. Also mapped to PLO6 (0.6) as engaging in scholarship requires a strong knowledge base.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(468, 52, 1, 2, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO5, which focuses on systematic examination to arrive at data-informed decisions.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(469, 52, 1, 3, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO2 and PLO5, as planning effective instruction and making data-informed decisions are core problem-solving activities in an educational context.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(470, 52, 1, 4, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO6 (engaging in scholarship) and strongly (0.6) to PLO3 (using emerging technologies), as both require research and adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(471, 52, 2, 8, 'Mapped moderately (0.5) to PLO6, as active engagement in scholarship implies a desire for lifelong learning.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(472, 52, 4, 13, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO4, which is centered on fostering successful learning experiences by addressing individual differences.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(473, 52, 4, 14, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO7, which explicitly requires the application of professional ethics.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(474, 52, 5, 19, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO2, as planning effective instruction is a key management function.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(475, 52, 5, 21, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO8, which focuses on leading positive change in education.', '', '2026-02-20 13:38:45', '2026-02-20 13:38:45'),
(476, 54, 1, 1, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO1, as it directly involves understanding key theories and concepts. Also mapped to PLO6 (0.6) as engaging in scholarship requires a strong knowledge base.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(477, 54, 1, 2, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO5, which focuses on systematic analysis to make well-informed decisions.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(478, 54, 1, 3, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO2 and PLO5, as developing effective instruction plans and making informed decisions are core problem-solving activities in a coaching context.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(479, 54, 1, 4, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO6 (engaging in scholarship) and strongly (0.6) to PLO3 (using emerging technologies), as both require research and adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(480, 54, 2, 8, 'Mapped moderately (0.5) to PLO6, as active engagement in scholarship implies a desire for lifelong learning.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(481, 54, 4, 13, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO4, which is centered on catering to individual differences among students.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(482, 54, 4, 14, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO7, which explicitly requires the application of professional ethics.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(483, 54, 5, 19, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO2, as developing plans for instruction is a key management function.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(484, 54, 5, 21, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO8, which focuses on leading positive change in education.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:09', '2026-02-20 13:39:09'),
(485, 53, 1, 1, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO1, which focuses on demonstrating knowledge and competencies in sport management.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(486, 53, 1, 2, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO3, which explicitly requires applying critical thinking and reasoning skills. Also mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO5, as data analysis requires critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(487, 53, 1, 3, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO2, as applying knowledge and skills in real-world settings is a problem-solving activity.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(488, 53, 1, 4, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO5, which involves collecting and analyzing data, a core research activity.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(489, 53, 3, 10, 'Mapped at 1.0 to PLO4, which is centered on oral and written communication.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(490, 53, 3, 11, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO3, which requires application into local, regional, and international contexts.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(491, 53, 4, 14, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO3, which includes awareness of ethical and legal issues.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(492, 53, 5, 19, 'Mapped strongly (0.7) to PLO1, as the PLO is about demonstrating competencies in sport management.', '', '2026-02-20 13:39:31', '2026-02-20 13:39:31'),
(493, 6, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (40%)** and **PLO2 (30%)** providing the core knowledge of biological sciences. The other PLOs ensure students can apply and communicate their mastery.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(494, 6, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to biological sciences. **PLO4 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to engage in critical thinking on problem solving activities. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the theoretical and practical context for critical analysis.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(495, 6, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving is a key focus of this program. **PLO4 (50%)** is central, as it requires students to engage in problem solving activities. **PLO3 (20%)** provides the practical skills for problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(496, 6, 1, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO3 (40%)**, which focuses on instrumentation and research techniques. **PLO4 (30%)** contributes by encouraging novel and adaptive approaches to problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44');
INSERT INTO `justifications` (`id`, `programId`, `gaId`, `competencyId`, `textEn`, `textAr`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`) VALUES
(497, 6, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own critical thinking and communication skills. **PLO4 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to engage in critical thinking. **PLO5 (15%)** and **PLO6 (15%)** contribute by providing opportunities for self-reflection on communication skills.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(498, 6, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse biological concepts and research techniques. **PLO3 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to adapt to different instrumentation and techniques. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the conceptual and problem-solving skills for adaptability.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(499, 6, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO3 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to think adaptively about research techniques. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the conceptual and problem-solving skills for adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(500, 6, 2, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO3 (40%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to use instrumentation and proper techniques in biological sciences research. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by encouraging students to engage in critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(501, 6, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (50%)**, which requires students to describe the interactions between organisms and their environments, and **PLO1 (20%)**, which provides the foundational knowledge of biological sciences.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(502, 6, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (40%)** and **PLO6 (40%)**, which are dedicated to demonstrating proficiency in written and oral communication. The other PLOs provide the knowledge base for effective communication.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(503, 6, 3, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (60%)**, which requires students to describe the interactions between organisms and their environments, providing a context for understanding local and international environmental issues.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(504, 6, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills within the context of Qatari and Arab society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(505, 6, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (60%)**, which requires students to describe the interactions between organisms and their environments, providing a context for understanding biodiversity.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(506, 6, 4, 14, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on proper research techniques. **PLO3 (40%)** is key, as it requires students to use instrumentation and proper techniques correctly. **PLO4 (20%)** provides the context for ethical decision-making in problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(507, 6, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the study of organism-environment interactions. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the research and problem-solving skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(508, 6, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to problem-solving. **PLO3 (30%)** contributes by providing the practical skills to implement creative solutions.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(509, 6, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(510, 6, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Biological Sciences program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(511, 6, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(512, 6, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Biological Sciences program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-20 14:33:14', '2026-02-21 11:33:44'),
(598, 8, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (30%)** providing the core knowledge of environmental sciences. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO7 (20%)** ensure a deep understanding of environmental degradation and contemporary issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(513, 7, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (30%)** providing the core knowledge of chemistry. **PLO3 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO5 (20%)** ensure a deep understanding of analytical techniques, literature search methods, and research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(514, 7, 1, 2, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (50%)**, which is dedicated to applying critical thinking and demonstrating problem-solving skills. The other PLOs provide the context for applying critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(515, 7, 1, 3, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (50%)**, which is dedicated to applying critical thinking and demonstrating problem-solving skills. The other PLOs provide the context for applying problem-solving skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(516, 7, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO5 (40%)**, which focuses on conducting research. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by providing the practical and literature research skills for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(517, 7, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own ethical standards and professional behavior. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to this process.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(518, 7, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse analytical techniques and research methods. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective chemical analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(519, 7, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar research problems. **PLO5 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to think adaptively about research. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the conceptual and practical skills for adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(520, 7, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO4 (30%)** and **PLO5 (30%)** are key, as they equip students with the ability to use modern literature search methods and conduct research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(521, 7, 3, 9, 'This competency is developed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of chemistry on society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(522, 7, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (50%)**, which is dedicated to communicating results to chemists and non-chemists. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by requiring students to write reports.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(523, 7, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of chemistry on society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(524, 7, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO5 (30%)**, which requires students to document findings according to professional and ethical standards, and **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)**, which provide the context for understanding and applying these standards in a culturally sensitive manner.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(525, 7, 4, 13, 'This competency is developed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of chemistry on society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(526, 7, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (40%)**, which requires students to document findings according to professional and ethical standards. **PLO2 (30%)** contributes by requiring students to apply proper procedures and regulations.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(527, 7, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the safe handling and use of chemicals. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the research and ethical skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(528, 7, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the safe handling and use of chemicals. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the research and ethical skills to support community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(529, 7, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO5 (40%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to research. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** contribute by providing the problem-solving and practical skills to implement creative solutions.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(530, 7, 5, 18, 'This competency is explicitly addressed by **PLO3 (100%)**, which requires students to work in teams.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(531, 7, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Chemistry program. The PLOs do not address management skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(532, 7, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through teamwork, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(533, 7, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Chemistry program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:17:22', '2026-02-21 11:34:07'),
(534, 18, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (40%)** providing the core knowledge of psychology\'s major content domains. **PLO2 (30%)** builds on this by applying psychological concepts. The other PLOs ensure students can apply and communicate their mastery.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(535, 18, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to psychology. **PLO2 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to apply psychological concepts to explain various processes. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the theoretical and research context for critical analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(536, 18, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying psychological concepts and research methods. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO3 (30%)** are central, as they require students to apply concepts and use research to solve problems. **PLO4 (20%)** adds a practical dimension to problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(537, 18, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO3 (50%)**, which is entirely focused on research methodology. The other PLOs contribute by providing the subject-matter knowledge and analytical skills necessary for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(538, 18, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own ethical standards and professional behavior. **PLO5 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to apply professional ethical standards. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by providing psychological and practical context for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(539, 18, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse psychological concepts and intervention methods. **PLO4 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to develop a working knowledge of intervention methods that can be adapted to different situations. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the conceptual and research skills for adaptability.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(540, 18, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO4 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to think adaptively about psychological interventions. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the conceptual and research skills for adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(541, 18, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO3 (40%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to use effective research methodology. **PLO5 (20%)** contributes by encouraging students to evaluate psychological science and practice.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(542, 18, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (40%)**, which requires students to apply psychological concepts to explain social processes, and **PLO1 (20%)**, which provides the foundational knowledge of psychology\'s major content domains.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(543, 18, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (50%)**, which is dedicated to writing scientific arguments and presenting information orally. The other PLOs provide the knowledge base for effective communication.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(544, 18, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (40%)**, which requires students to apply psychological concepts to explain social processes, and **PLO1 (20%)**, which provides the foundational knowledge of psychology\'s major content domains.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(545, 18, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO2 (30%)**, which requires students to apply psychological concepts to explain social processes, and **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)**, which provide the context for understanding and applying these concepts in a culturally sensitive manner.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(546, 18, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (40%)**, which requires students to apply psychological concepts to explain social processes, and **PLO1 (20%)**, which provides the foundational knowledge of psychology\'s major content domains.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(547, 18, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (50%)**, which requires students to apply professional ethical standards to evaluate psychological science and practice. The other PLOs provide the context for ethical decision-making.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(548, 18, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the application of psychological concepts to social processes. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the research and practical skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(549, 18, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the application of psychological concepts to social processes. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the research and practical skills to support community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(550, 18, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO3 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to research. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by providing the conceptual and practical skills to support creative work.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(551, 18, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(552, 18, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Psychology program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in industrial-organizational psychology or business programs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(553, 18, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions, role-playing, and practical exercises, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(554, 18, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Psychology program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:21:41', '2026-02-21 14:21:41'),
(555, 14, 1, 1, 'This competency is developed through a combination of foundational skills and specialized knowledge. **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)** provide the core knowledge of spatial analysis and problem-solving. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** ensure that students can effectively apply this knowledge in research and modeling.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(556, 14, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to this program. **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)** are key, as they require students to think critically about spatial structures and real-world problems. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the research and modeling skills to support critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(557, 14, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving is a key focus of this program. **PLO2 (40%)** is central to this competency, as it requires students to solve real-world problems. **PLO1 (30%)** provides the analytical tools for problem-solving, while **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (10%)** provide supporting research and modeling skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(558, 14, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO3 (50%)**, which is entirely focused on research methods. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide opportunities to apply research skills to real-world problems and modeling scenarios.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(559, 14, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own role in solving real-world problems. **PLO2 (40%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to consider the social and environmental impact of their work. The other PLOs provide supporting skills for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(560, 14, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse real-world problems. **PLO2 (40%)** and **PLO1 (30%)** are key, as they require students to adapt their analytical approaches to different environmental, economic, and social contexts.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(561, 14, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO2 (40%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to think adaptively about how to solve real-world problems. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the analytical and research skills for adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(562, 14, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research and analytical skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO4 (30%)** are key, as they equip students with the ability to acquire, analyze, and evaluate geographic data and modeling techniques.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(563, 14, 3, 9, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse cultural contexts. **PLO2 (40%)** and **PLO1 (30%)** are key, as they require students to consider the cultural dimensions of real-world problems and human settlements.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(564, 14, 3, 10, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on communicating research findings and problem-solving approaches. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO3 (30%)** are key, as they require students to synthesize and communicate geospatial knowledge. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide supporting skills for communicating spatial analysis and modeling results.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(565, 14, 4, 11, 'This competency is primarily addressed by **PLO2 (50%)**, which requires students to solve real-world problems in Qatar and beyond. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the analytical and research skills to understand these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(566, 14, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO2 (50%)**, which provides opportunities to apply geospatial knowledge to problems in Qatar and the broader Islamic world. This allows students to explore and articulate their own identity in relation to their local and regional context.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(567, 14, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (50%)**, which exposes students to a wide range of social, economic, and environmental contexts. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** contribute by providing the analytical and research skills to understand and appreciate diversity.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(568, 14, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO3 (50%)**, which requires students to acquire, analyze, and interpret data in an ethical and professional manner. **PLO2 (30%)** provides the context for ethical decision-making in real-world problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(569, 14, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (50%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through problem-solving. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the analytical and research skills to understand and address these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(570, 14, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (50%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through problem-solving. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the analytical and research skills to understand and address these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(571, 14, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO2 (50%)**, which encourages creative and innovative solutions to real-world problems. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the tools and research skills to support creative problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(572, 14, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual research and analysis. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(573, 14, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Applied Geography and GIS program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(574, 14, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(575, 14, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Applied Geography and GIS program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:27:38', '2026-02-21 12:38:26'),
(576, 12, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (30%)** providing the core skills in using the Arabic language. **PLO3 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO5 (20%)** ensure a deep understanding of linguistic and literary heritage, trends, and schools of thought.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(577, 12, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is developed across the curriculum. **PLO3 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, **PLO5 (20%)**, and **PLO6 (20%)** all contribute by requiring students to analyze, distinguish, and apply critical thinking to literary and linguistic concepts.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(578, 12, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying linguistic and literary knowledge. **PLO6 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to apply their skills in research, analysis, and criticism. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the context for problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(579, 12, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO6 (30%)**, which focuses on research, analysis, and criticism. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the foundational skills and knowledge for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(580, 12, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own cultural and linguistic identity. **PLO2 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to express the needs of their community. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO6 (20%)** contribute by providing opportunities for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(581, 12, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse literary and linguistic trends. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective linguistic and literary analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(582, 12, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar texts and contexts. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptive thinking skills necessary for effective linguistic and literary analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(583, 12, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO3 (30%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to use linguistic and literary heritage sources. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by encouraging students to engage with the language and its literature.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(584, 12, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO3 (30%)**, which focus on expressing the needs of the community and using linguistic and literary heritage sources.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(585, 12, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (50%)**, which is dedicated to showing high efficiency in the use of Arabic language. **PLO2 (30%)** contributes by requiring students to employ Arabic in writing, reading, and thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(586, 12, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (40%)**, which requires students to express the needs of the local, Arab, and Islamic community. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the context for understanding these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(587, 12, 4, 12, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO2 (50%)**, which requires students to express the needs of the local, Arab, and Islamic community. **PLO3 (20%)** contributes by improving the use of linguistic and literary heritage sources.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(588, 12, 4, 13, 'This competency is developed through exposure to different artistic trends and linguistic schools. **PLO4 (30%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** are key, as they require students to distinguish between different trends and schools of thought.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(589, 12, 4, 14, 'This competency is developed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills in a professional and ethical manner. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(590, 12, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (50%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the expression of community needs. The other PLOs provide the skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(591, 12, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (50%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the expression of community needs. The other PLOs provide the skills to support community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(592, 12, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO6 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to research, analysis, and criticism. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by providing opportunities to apply creative thinking to literary and linguistic analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(593, 12, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(594, 12, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Arabic Language program. The PLOs do not address management skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(595, 12, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(596, 12, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Arabic Language program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:32:58', '2026-02-21 14:32:58'),
(597, 6, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the study of organism-environment interactions. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the research and problem-solving skills to support community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:33:43', '2026-02-21 14:33:43'),
(599, 8, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is developed across the curriculum. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the critical thinking skills necessary for effective environmental analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(600, 8, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying environmental science concepts to real-world issues. **PLO2 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to explain the underlying causes for environmental degradation. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the practical and research skills for problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(601, 8, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO3 (30%)** and **PLO4 (30%)**, which focus on conducting experiments and employing scientific approaches in research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(602, 8, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own ethical standards and professional behavior. **PLO4 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to be aware of risk assessment, health and safety regulations, and environmental laws. **PLO5 (20%)** contributes by providing opportunities for self-reflection on the human dimensions of the profession.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(603, 8, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse environmental concepts and research techniques. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective environmental analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(604, 8, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar environmental challenges. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptive thinking skills necessary for effective environmental analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(605, 8, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO3 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO7 (20%)** are key, as they equip students with the ability to conduct experiments, employ scientific approaches, and explain contemporary and emerging environmental issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(606, 8, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO5 (50%)**, which requires students to explain the human dimensions in their profession, including diverse social, cultural, economic, and international aspects.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(607, 8, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (60%)**, which is dedicated to applying skilled delivery using verbal, written and electronic communication to convey environmental issues. **PLO5 (20%)** contributes by providing the knowledge base for effective communication.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(608, 8, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO5 (30%)**, which requires students to explain the human dimensions in their profession, and **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO7 (20%)**, which provide the context for understanding local and international environmental issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(609, 8, 4, 12, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO5 (40%)**, which requires students to explain the human dimensions in their profession, including diverse social, cultural, economic, and international aspects. **PLO4 (20%)** provides the context for understanding the impact of environmental issues on local and regional culture.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(610, 8, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO5 (40%)**, which requires students to explain the human dimensions in their profession, including diverse social, cultural, economic, and international aspects. **PLO4 (20%)** provides the context for understanding the impact of environmental issues on diverse communities.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(611, 8, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO4 (50%)**, which requires students to employ scientific approaches in a safe and ethical manner. **PLO3 (20%)** provides the context for ethical decision-making in research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(612, 8, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the study of environmental degradation. **PLO4 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the research and social skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(613, 8, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the study of environmental degradation. **PLO4 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the research and social skills to support community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(614, 8, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO4 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to research. **PLO3 (20%)** contributes by providing the practical skills to implement creative solutions.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(615, 8, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(616, 8, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Environmental Sciences program. The PLOs do not address management skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(617, 8, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(618, 8, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Environmental Sciences program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:27', '2026-02-21 14:34:27'),
(619, 4, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (40%)** providing the core theoretical knowledge of art history and theories. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** build on this by adding cross-cultural and practical knowledge. **PLO4 (10%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** ensure students can apply and communicate their mastery.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(620, 4, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to fine arts. **PLO3 (40%)** is key, as it requires students to develop critical knowledge and skills. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO2 (20%)** provide the theoretical and cultural context for critical analysis, while **PLO4 (10%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** provide opportunities to apply these skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(621, 4, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves creative and practical challenges. **PLO3 (30%)** and **PLO5 (30%)** are central, as they require students to solve problems in making and displaying art. **PLO4 (20%)** adds a research-based dimension to problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(622, 4, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO4 (40%)**, which focuses on research and communication. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** contribute by encouraging novel and adaptive approaches to art-making.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(623, 4, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to develop their own artistic voice. **PLO5 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to design a portfolio that represents their creativity. **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by providing cultural and critical context for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(624, 4, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse cultural and artistic contexts. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO3 (30%)** are key, as they require students to adapt their artistic practice to different cultural and material conditions.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(625, 4, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar artistic challenges. **PLO3 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to think adaptively about making and displaying art. **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO5 (20%)** provide supporting skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(626, 4, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with a broad theoretical and practical foundation. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to fostering a desire for continuous learning and artistic development.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(627, 4, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (40%)** and **PLO1 (30%)**, which focus on understanding cross-cultural relations and art history. **PLO4 (20%)** adds a specific focus on Qatari culture.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(628, 4, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO4 (60%)**, which is dedicated to developing clear and persuasive communication in written, visual, and oral forms. The other PLOs contribute by providing the knowledge and skills to be communicated.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(629, 4, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (50%)**, which focuses on cross-cultural relations, and **PLO4 (20%)**, which adds a specific focus on Qatari culture. **PLO1 (20%)** provides the historical context for understanding local and international issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(630, 4, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO4 (60%)**, which requires students to communicate findings relevant to Qatari culture. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO1 (10%)** provide a broader cultural and historical context for understanding this identity.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(631, 4, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (60%)**, which focuses on cross-cultural relations. **PLO4 (20%)** adds a specific focus on diversity within Qatari culture.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(632, 4, 4, 14, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on critical self-reflection and responsible art-making. **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO4 (30%)** are key, as they require students to consider the ethical implications of their work.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(633, 4, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO4 (50%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through art that is relevant to Qatari culture. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the cultural and critical skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(634, 4, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (40%)** and **PLO4 (30%)**, which encourage students to engage with global and local communities through art. **PLO3 (20%)** provides the practical skills for community-based art projects.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(635, 4, 5, 17, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (50%)**, which is dedicated to developing a creative and independent artistic portfolio. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO4 (10%)** contribute by providing the critical and communication skills to support creative work.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(636, 4, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual artistic development. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class critiques and group exhibitions, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(637, 4, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Fine Arts program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in arts administration or business programs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(638, 4, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions, critiques, and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(639, 4, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Fine Arts program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:34:52', '2026-02-21 14:34:52'),
(640, 9, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (30%)** providing the core knowledge of mathematical arguments. **PLO2 (20%)** ensures a deep understanding of mathematical models.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(641, 9, 1, 2, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (40%)**, which is dedicated to formulating and examining the correctness of mathematical arguments. **PLO2 (20%)** provides the context for applying critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(642, 9, 1, 3, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (30%)**, which is dedicated to applying appropriate problem-solving strategies. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the context for applying problem-solving skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(643, 9, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO8 (40%)**, which focuses on making contributions to research projects and new applications. The other PLOs provide the foundational skills for research.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(644, 9, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own mathematical reasoning. **PLO1 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to formulate and examine the correctness of mathematical arguments.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(645, 9, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse mathematical models and problem-solving strategies. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** are key, as they require students to adapt to different models and perspectives.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(646, 9, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar problems. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** are key, as they require students to think adaptively about mathematical models and problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(647, 9, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO8 (30%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to make contributions to research projects and new applications.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(648, 9, 3, 9, 'This competency is developed through **PLO2 (30%)**, which requires students to analyze mathematical models from real life-problems, providing a context for understanding the cultural dimensions of mathematics.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(649, 9, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO4 (60%)**, which is dedicated to communicating mathematical ideas orally and in writing.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(650, 9, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (40%)**, which requires students to analyze mathematical models from real life-problems, providing a context for understanding local and international issues.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(651, 9, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills within the context of Qatari and Arab society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(652, 9, 4, 13, 'This competency is developed through **PLO2 (30%)**, which requires students to analyze mathematical models from real life-problems, providing a context for understanding diverse perspectives.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(653, 9, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (30%)**, which requires students to formulate and examine the correctness of mathematical arguments, instilling a sense of professional responsibility.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(654, 9, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the analysis of mathematical models from real life-problems.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(655, 9, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the analysis of mathematical models from real life-problems.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11');
INSERT INTO `justifications` (`id`, `programId`, `gaId`, `competencyId`, `textEn`, `textAr`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`) VALUES
(656, 9, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO8 (40%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to research and new applications. The other PLOs provide the foundational skills for creativity and innovation.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(657, 9, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(658, 9, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Mathematics program. The PLOs do not address management skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(659, 9, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(660, 9, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Mathematics program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills.', '', '2026-02-21 14:35:11', '2026-02-21 14:35:11'),
(661, 10, 1, 1, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (50%)**, which is dedicated to demonstrating a well-founded Knowledge and Application of Fundamental Concepts of Physics. **PLO2 (20%)** ensures a deep understanding of mathematical solutions.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(662, 10, 1, 2, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO2 (40%)**, which is dedicated to analyzing physics related problems to formulate appropriate mathematical solutions. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the context for applying critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(663, 10, 1, 3, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO2 (40%)** and **PLO3 (30%)**, which are dedicated to analyzing physics related problems and utilizing software and computational skills to solve them.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(664, 10, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO3 (30%)** and **PLO4 (30%)**, which focus on utilizing software and computational skills and illustrating experimental skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(665, 10, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own ethical standards. **PLO6 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to demonstrate high ethical standards. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO2 (20%)** contribute by providing opportunities for self-reflection on their knowledge and analytical skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(666, 10, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse physical problems and experimental techniques. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective physical analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(667, 10, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar problems. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptive thinking skills necessary for effective physical analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(668, 10, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to this process.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(669, 10, 3, 9, 'This competency is developed through **PLO1 (30%)**, which requires students to demonstrate a well-founded Knowledge and Application of Fundamental Concepts of Physics, providing a context for understanding the cultural dimensions of physics.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(670, 10, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (60%)**, which is dedicated to communicating the Experimental and Theoretical Results in Written and Oral Forms.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(671, 10, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (30%)**, which requires students to demonstrate a well-founded Knowledge and Application of Fundamental Concepts of Physics, providing a context for understanding local and international issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(672, 10, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO6 (30%)**, which requires students to demonstrate high ethical standards, and **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO2 (20%)**, which provide the context for understanding and applying these standards in a culturally sensitive manner.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(673, 10, 4, 13, 'This competency is developed through **PLO1 (30%)**, which requires students to demonstrate a well-founded Knowledge and Application of Fundamental Concepts of Physics, providing a context for understanding diverse perspectives.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(674, 10, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (50%)**, which requires students to demonstrate high ethical standards.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(675, 10, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of physics on society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(676, 10, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of physics on society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(677, 10, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO3 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to solving physical problems. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by providing the analytical and experimental skills to implement creative solutions.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(678, 10, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(679, 10, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Physics program. The PLOs do not address management skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(680, 10, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(681, 10, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Physics program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:35:52', '2026-02-21 15:35:52'),
(682, 3, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (30%)** providing the core knowledge of fundamental concepts and research methods. The other PLOs ensure students can apply and communicate their mastery across various policy domains.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(683, 3, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to policy analysis. **PLO2 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to analyze and synthesize information to assess policy options. **PLO1 (20%)** provides the research methods to support critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(684, 3, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving is a key focus of this program. **PLO2 (40%)** is central, as it requires students to solve problems in public policy. The other PLOs provide the context for problem-solving in specific policy domains.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(685, 3, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO1 (30%)**, which is focused on research methods. **PLO2 (20%)** contributes by providing opportunities to apply research skills to policy problems.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(686, 3, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own role in policy-making and the societal impact of their work. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to this process.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(687, 3, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse policy domains. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective policy analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(688, 3, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar policy challenges. **PLO2 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to think adaptively about policy options. **PLO4 (20%)** provides the context for adaptive thinking in relation to societal determinants.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(689, 3, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO1 (30%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to identify and explain fundamental concepts and research methods.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(690, 3, 3, 9, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse societal determinants and policy contexts. **PLO4 (20%)**, **PLO5 (20%)**, and **PLO6 (20%)** are key, as they require students to consider the cultural dimensions of policy-making.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(691, 3, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO3 (60%)**, which is dedicated to communicating complex ideas clearly and persuasively. The other PLOs provide the knowledge base for effective communication.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(692, 3, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO4 (20%)**, **PLO5 (20%)**, and **PLO6 (20%)**, which require students to analyze societal determinants and evaluate the impact of policy decisions on local and global issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(693, 3, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO4 (30%)**, which requires students to analyze societal determinants, and **PLO6 (20%)**, which provides the context for understanding the impact of policy decisions on local and regional culture.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(694, 3, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO4 (30%)**, which requires students to analyze societal determinants, and **PLO6 (20%)**, which provides the context for understanding the impact of policy decisions on diverse communities.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(695, 3, 4, 14, 'This competency is developed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills in a professional and ethical manner. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(696, 3, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO4 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the analysis of societal determinants. **PLO2 (20%)** provides the skills to support civic engagement through policy analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(697, 3, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO4 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the analysis of societal determinants. **PLO2 (20%)** provides the skills to support community and global engagement through policy analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(698, 3, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to solving problems in public policy. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by providing opportunities to apply creative thinking to policy design.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(699, 3, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(700, 3, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Policy, Planning and Development program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in public administration or business programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(701, 3, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(702, 3, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Policy, Planning and Development program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:16', '2026-02-21 15:36:16'),
(703, 17, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO3 (40%)** providing the core knowledge of social work practice. **PLO4 (20%)** adds a theoretical dimension, while the other PLOs provide supporting skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(704, 17, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to social work. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the critical thinking skills necessary for effective practice.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(705, 17, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving is a key focus of this program. **PLO3 (30%)** and **PLO4 (30%)** are central, as they require students to apply knowledge and evaluate strategies to solve social problems.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(706, 17, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO5 (40%)**, which is entirely focused on research skills. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by encouraging students to evaluate and adapt strategies for social problems.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(707, 17, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own cultural and ethical perspectives. **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)** are central to this process, as they require students to analyze the role of culture and ethics in social work.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(708, 17, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse cultural and social contexts. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective social work practice.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(709, 17, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptive thinking skills necessary for effective social work practice.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(710, 17, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO5 (40%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to employ effective research skills. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by encouraging students to evaluate and adapt strategies.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(711, 17, 3, 9, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (60%)**, which is dedicated to analyzing the role of culture in social work. The other PLOs provide supporting skills for culturally competent practice.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(712, 17, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (50%)**, which is dedicated to applying effective communication skills in social work practice. The other PLOs provide the knowledge base for effective communication.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(713, 17, 4, 11, 'This competency is primarily addressed by **PLO4 (50%)**, which requires students to evaluate strategies to respond to local and global community socio-economic challenges. **PLO1 (20%)** provides the cultural context for understanding these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(714, 17, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO1 (40%)**, which requires students to analyze the role of culture in social work, and **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)**, which provide the ethical and practical context for applying this understanding in a culturally sensitive manner.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(715, 17, 4, 13, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (60%)**, which is dedicated to analyzing the role of culture in social work. The other PLOs provide supporting skills for working with diverse populations.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(716, 17, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO2 (60%)**, which requires students to apply the roles of ethics in social work practice. The other PLOs provide the context for ethical decision-making.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(717, 17, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the evaluation of strategies to respond to community challenges. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO2 (20%)** provide the cultural and ethical framework for civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(718, 17, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO4 (50%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the evaluation of strategies to respond to community challenges. **PLO1 (20%)** provides the cultural context for community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(719, 17, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to solving social problems. **PLO3 (20%)** contributes by providing the practical skills to implement creative solutions.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(720, 17, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and field placements, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(721, 17, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Social Work program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in social work administration or policy programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(722, 17, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions, role-playing, and field placements, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(723, 17, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Social Work program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through advanced practice or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:36:57', '2026-02-21 15:36:57'),
(724, 16, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)** providing the core knowledge of sociological concepts and phenomena. The other PLOs ensure students can apply and communicate their mastery.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(725, 16, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to sociology. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the critical thinking skills necessary for effective sociological analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(726, 16, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying sociological concepts and research methods to social issues. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the problem-solving skills necessary for effective sociological analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(727, 16, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO3 (40%)**, which is entirely focused on research methodology. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by providing opportunities to apply research skills to social and cultural issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(728, 16, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own ethical standards and cultural perspectives. **PLO5 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to apply an international code of ethics. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO2 (20%)** contribute by providing cultural and social context for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(729, 16, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse social and cultural contexts. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptability necessary for effective sociological analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(730, 16, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. The even distribution of weights reflects the fact that all PLOs contribute to developing the adaptive thinking skills necessary for effective sociological analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(731, 16, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO3 (40%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to design an appropriate methodology to conduct sociological research. **PLO4 (20%)** contributes by encouraging students to analyze quantitative and qualitative data.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(732, 16, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO1 (40%)** and **PLO2 (30%)**, which focus on identifying and explaining social and cultural concepts and phenomena.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(733, 16, 3, 10, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on communicating sociological analysis. **PLO4 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to analyze and communicate data on social and cultural issues. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO6 (20%)** provide supporting skills for communicating research and theory.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(734, 16, 4, 11, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (50%)**, which requires students to apply sociological theories to local, regional, and international social issues. The other PLOs provide the context for understanding these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(735, 16, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills within the context of Qatari and Arab society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(736, 16, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO1 (40%)** and **PLO2 (30%)**, which focus on identifying and explaining social and cultural concepts and phenomena.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(737, 16, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (50%)**, which requires students to apply an international code of ethics to study social problems. The other PLOs provide the context for ethical decision-making.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(738, 16, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO6 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with civic issues through the application of sociological theories. **PLO4 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the research and ethical skills to support civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(739, 16, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO6 (30%)**, which encourages students to engage with community and global issues through the application of sociological theories. **PLO4 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the research and ethical skills to support community and global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(740, 16, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO3 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to research design. **PLO4 (20%)** and **PLO6 (20%)** contribute by providing opportunities to apply creative thinking to data analysis and theoretical application.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(741, 16, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(742, 16, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Sociology program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(743, 16, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(744, 16, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Sociology program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:21', '2026-02-21 15:37:21'),
(745, 11, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational, with **PLO6 (30%)** providing the theoretical basis of statistical methods. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO2 (20%)** ensure a deep understanding of data collection and experimental design.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(746, 11, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is developed across the curriculum. **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO7 (20%)** are key, as they require students to use relevant experimental design, analyze data, and provide alternative techniques for data analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(747, 11, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying statistical principles to real-world problems. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO7 (20%)** are key, as they require students to collect data, use relevant experimental design, analyze data, and provide alternative techniques for data analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(748, 11, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO2 (30%)**, which focuses on experimental design. **PLO1 (20%)** and **PLO7 (20%)** contribute by providing the data collection and analytical skills for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(749, 11, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own communication and ethical standards. **PLO5 (30%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to communicate effectively with statistics users. **PLO6 (20%)** contributes by providing opportunities for self-reflection on the theoretical basis of statistical methods.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(750, 11, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse data types and analytical techniques. **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO7 (20%)** are key, as they require students to adapt to different experimental designs, data types, and analytical techniques.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(751, 11, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar data sets. **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO7 (20%)** are key, as they require students to think adaptively about experimental design, data analysis, and analytical techniques.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(752, 11, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the theoretical knowledge necessary for continuous learning. **PLO6 (30%)** is key, as it equips students with the theoretical basis of statistical methods. **PLO2 (20%)** contributes by encouraging students to use relevant experimental design.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(753, 11, 3, 9, 'This competency is developed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of statistics on society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(754, 11, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (70%)**, which is dedicated to communicating effectively with statistics users. **PLO3 (20%)** contributes by requiring students to describe various types of data numerically and graphically.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(755, 11, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of statistics on society. **PLO2 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to use relevant experimental design for scientific investigations.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(756, 11, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills within the context of Qatari and Arab society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(757, 11, 4, 13, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to understand the impact of statistics on society. **PLO2 (30%)** is key, as it requires students to use relevant experimental design for scientific investigations.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(758, 11, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (30%)**, which requires students to collect data that conform with the statistical principles. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** contribute by requiring students to use relevant experimental design and communicate effectively with statistics users.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(759, 11, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourage students to engage with civic issues through the collection and analysis of data.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(760, 11, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)**, which encourage students to engage with community and global issues through the collection and analysis of data.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(761, 11, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO7 (30%)**, which encourages creative and innovative approaches to data analysis. **PLO2 (20%)** contributes by providing opportunities to apply creative thinking to experimental design.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(762, 11, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual knowledge and skills. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(763, 11, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Statistics program. The PLOs do not address management skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(764, 11, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through communication with statistics users, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(765, 11, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Statistics program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:37:51', '2026-02-21 15:37:51'),
(766, 1, 1, 1, 'This competency is developed through a combination of foundational skills and specialized knowledge. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** provide the core theoretical and practical knowledge of linguistics and literary analysis. **PLO1 (20%)** ensures that students can effectively communicate their understanding, while **PLO4 (20%)** allows them to apply their knowledge to specific literary genres. **PLO3 (10%)** provides a broader contextual understanding that enhances their mastery of the subject.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(767, 1, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is a central skill in this program. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO4 (30%)** are key to developing these skills, as they require students to analyze linguistic data and literary texts in a critical and systematic way. **PLO3 (20%)** further enhances this skill by encouraging students to think critically about the relationship between language, literature, and society. **PLO1 (10%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** provide the foundational communication and theoretical skills necessary for effective critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(768, 1, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying analytical tools to complex linguistic and literary phenomena. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO3 (30%)** are central to this competency, as they equip students with the tools and contextual understanding to solve problems in language and literature. **PLO4 (20%)** provides opportunities to apply these skills to specific literary problems, while **PLO1 (10%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** provide supporting skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(769, 1, 2, 4, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on research and analysis. **PLO4 (30%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** are key, as they require students to engage with theoretical knowledge and apply it to research questions. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** provide the analytical and contextual skills necessary for effective research, and **PLO1 (10%)** ensures that students can communicate their research findings.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(770, 1, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own cultural and linguistic perspectives. **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO4 (30%)** are central to this process, as they expose students to a wide range of cultural and historical contexts. The remaining PLOs provide supporting skills for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(771, 1, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse linguistic and literary contexts. **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO2 (20%)** are key, as they require students to adapt their analytical approaches to different languages and cultural contexts. **PLO4 (20%)** further enhances this skill by encouraging students to adapt their critical perspectives to different literary genres and historical periods.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(772, 1, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO3 (30%)** and **PLO4 (30%)** are central to this process, as they require students to think adaptively about the relationship between language, literature, and society. **PLO2 (20%)** provides the analytical tools for adaptive thinking, while **PLO1 (10%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** provide supporting skills.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(773, 1, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research and analytical skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO5 (30%)** is key, as it equips students with the theoretical knowledge and practical methods to pursue further studies. **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** contribute by fostering a curiosity about language, literature, and culture.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(774, 1, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO3 (50%)** and **PLO4 (30%)**, which focus on understanding the social, cultural, and historical contexts of language and literature. **PLO1 (10%)** and **PLO2 (10%)** contribute by providing the communication and analytical skills to engage with different cultures.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(775, 1, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (60%)**, which is dedicated to developing clear and effective communication in English. All other PLOs contribute to this competency by providing students with specialized knowledge and analytical skills that they can then communicate to others.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(776, 1, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO3 (50%)** and **PLO4 (30%)**, which encourage students to engage with local and international issues through the lens of language and literature. By studying diverse cultures and societies, students develop a broader perspective on contemporary issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(777, 1, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO3 (50%)** and **PLO4 (50%)**, which provide opportunities to study Arabic and Islamic literature and culture within a broader global context. This allows students to explore and articulate their own identity in relation to other cultures.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(778, 1, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO4 (30%)**, which expose students to a wide range of cultures, languages, and perspectives. **PLO2 (20%)** contributes by providing the analytical tools to understand and appreciate linguistic diversity.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(779, 1, 4, 14, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on academic integrity and responsible research. **PLO2 (30%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** provide the foundational skills for ethical conduct in research and analysis. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the context for ethical decision-making in communication and cultural analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(780, 1, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourage students to engage with civic issues through the lens of language and literature. By studying the role of language and literature in society, students develop a sense of their civic responsibilities.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(781, 1, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourage students to engage with community and global issues through the lens of language and literature. By studying diverse cultures and societies, students develop a broader perspective and a sense of their role in a globalized world.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(782, 1, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourages creative and innovative interpretations of literary texts. **PLO2 (20%)** and **PLO3 (20%)** contribute by providing the analytical and contextual skills to support creative work, while **PLO1 (10%)** and **PLO5 (10%)** provide the communication and theoretical skills to express creative ideas.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(783, 1, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual research and analysis. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(784, 1, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the English Literature and Linguistics program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(785, 1, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(786, 1, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the English Literature and Linguistics program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:38:58', '2026-02-21 15:38:58'),
(787, 13, 1, 1, 'This competency is developed across all PLOs, with a strong emphasis on **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)**, which provide the core knowledge of historical analysis. **PLO5 (10%)** and **PLO6 (10%)** contribute by providing the skills to interpret and research historical facts.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(788, 13, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to the study of history. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** are key, as they require students to analyze and compare historical events and societies. **PLO5 (10%)** and **PLO6 (10%)** provide the skills to support critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(789, 13, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves interpreting historical evidence and drawing conclusions. **PLO5 (30%)** and **PLO6 (30%)** are central to this competency, as they equip students with the ability to interpret facts and synthesize information. The other PLOs provide the context for historical problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(790, 13, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO6 (50%)**, which is entirely focused on research methods. The other PLOs contribute by providing the subject-matter knowledge and analytical skills necessary for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(791, 13, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own cultural and historical perspectives. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** are central to this process, as they expose students to a wide range of cultures and historical periods.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(792, 13, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse historical contexts. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** are key, as they require students to adapt their analytical approaches to different societies and time periods.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(793, 13, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** are central to this process, as they require students to think adaptively about historical change and continuity.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(794, 13, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled primarily through **PLO6 (50%)**, which equips students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. The other PLOs contribute by fostering a curiosity about the past and a desire to learn more.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(795, 13, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO2 (40%)**, which focus on understanding global societies, cultures, and civilizations. The other PLOs contribute by providing the analytical skills to understand and appreciate different cultures.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(796, 13, 3, 10, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on communicating historical analysis. **PLO5 (30%)** and **PLO6 (30%)** are key, as they require students to interpret facts and synthesize information in a clear and persuasive manner. The other PLOs provide the knowledge base for effective communication.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(797, 13, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (40%)** and **PLO2 (40%)**, which encourage students to engage with global issues and diverse civilizations. The other PLOs contribute by providing the analytical skills to understand and address these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(798, 13, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO2 (60%)**, which has a special emphasis on Islamic History. The other PLOs contribute by providing a broader historical context for understanding this identity.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(799, 13, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO1 (40%)** and **PLO2 (40%)**, which expose students to a wide range of cultures and civilizations. The other PLOs contribute by providing the analytical skills to understand and appreciate diversity.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(800, 13, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO6 (50%)**, which requires students to conduct research in an ethical and professional manner. The other PLOs contribute by providing the context for ethical decision-making in historical analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(801, 13, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)**, which encourage students to engage with civic issues through the lens of history. By studying the past, students develop a sense of their civic responsibilities in the present.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(802, 13, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (40%)** and **PLO2 (40%)**, which encourage students to engage with global issues and diverse civilizations. The other PLOs contribute by providing the analytical skills to understand and address these issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(803, 13, 5, 17, 'This competency is developed through the program\'s emphasis on interpreting historical evidence and constructing historical narratives. **PLO3 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, **PLO5 (20%)**, and **PLO6 (20%)** all contribute to this competency by encouraging students to think creatively about the past.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(804, 13, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual research and analysis. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(805, 13, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the History program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(806, 13, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(807, 13, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the History program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:20', '2026-02-21 15:39:20'),
(808, 2, 1, 1, 'This competency is foundational to the program and is developed through multiple PLOs. **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** provide the core knowledge of global issues, regional perspectives, and Gulf politics. The other PLOs contribute by providing the skills to acquire and apply this knowledge effectively.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(809, 2, 1, 2, 'Critical thinking is central to analyzing international affairs. **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** are key, as they require students to analyze complex global issues and evaluate the impact of political and economic factors. The other PLOs provide supporting skills for critical analysis.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(810, 2, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying analytical skills to complex international issues. **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** are central to this competency, as they equip students with the ability to analyze and propose solutions to global problems. The other PLOs provide supporting skills for problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(811, 2, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO6 (40%)**, which is entirely focused on research methods. The other PLOs contribute by providing the subject-matter knowledge and analytical skills necessary for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42');
INSERT INTO `justifications` (`id`, `programId`, `gaId`, `competencyId`, `textEn`, `textAr`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`) VALUES
(812, 2, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own cultural and political perspectives. **PLO1 (30%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** are central to this process, as they expose students to a wide range of cultural and historical contexts.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(813, 2, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse political and cultural systems. **PLO1 (30%)**, **PLO3 (20%)**, and **PLO4 (20%)** are key, as they require students to adapt their analytical approaches to different regions and political contexts.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(814, 2, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO5 (20%)** are central to this process, as they require students to think adaptively about the impact of political and economic factors on global issues. **PLO6 (20%)** provides the research skills for adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(815, 2, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO6 (30%)** and **PLO2 (30%)** are key, as they equip students with the ability to conduct research and utilize information effectively.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(816, 2, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO1 (30%)**, which focus on understanding diverse cultures, histories, and perspectives from around the world. **PLO4 (30%)** adds a specific focus on the cultures of the Gulf region.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(817, 2, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO7 (40%)**, which is dedicated to developing clear, analytical, and persuasive communication. All other PLOs contribute by providing students with the knowledge and analytical skills that they need to communicate effectively.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(818, 2, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (30%)**, **PLO3 (30%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO5 (20%)**, which provide a comprehensive understanding of local, regional, and international issues.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(819, 2, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through **PLO4 (50%)**, which focuses on Gulf societies and politics, and **PLO3 (20%)**, which provides a broader understanding of regional histories and cultures. This allows students to explore and articulate their own identity in relation to the region.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(820, 2, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO3 (40%)** and **PLO1 (30%)**, which expose students to a wide range of cultures, histories, and perspectives. **PLO4 (30%)** adds a specific focus on the diversity within the Gulf region.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(821, 2, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO2 (60%)**, which requires students to use information ethically and responsibly. The other PLOs contribute by providing the context for ethical decision-making in international affairs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(822, 2, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO4 (40%)**, which encourage students to engage with civic issues at the global and local levels. **PLO3 (20%)** provides the historical context for civic engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(823, 2, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (40%)**, which focuses on global issues, and is supported by **PLO3 (20%)**, **PLO4 (20%)**, and **PLO5 (20%)**, which provide regional and thematic context for global engagement.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(824, 2, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO5 (30%)**, which encourage creative and innovative approaches to analyzing global issues. **PLO6 (20%)** contributes by providing the research skills to support creative work.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(825, 2, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual research and analysis. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(826, 2, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the International Affairs program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(827, 2, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(828, 2, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the International Affairs program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:39:42', '2026-02-21 15:39:42'),
(829, 15, 1, 1, 'This competency is developed across all PLOs, with each contributing a piece of the core knowledge and skills required for a career in mass communication. The even distribution of weights reflects the broad-based nature of this program.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(830, 15, 1, 2, 'This competency is honed through a combination of evaluative and analytical PLOs. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO7 (20%)** are central, as they require students to critically evaluate their own work and think independently. **PLO6 (15%)** contributes by developing research and evaluation skills, while **PLO4 (10%)** adds a theoretical dimension to critical thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(831, 15, 1, 3, 'Problem-solving in this context involves applying analytical and creative skills to communication challenges. **PLO3 (20%)** and **PLO7 (20%)** are key, as they require students to evaluate and solve problems of clarity, fairness, and style. **PLO6 (15%)** provides the research skills to support problem-solving.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(832, 15, 2, 4, 'This competency is most significantly developed through **PLO6 (30%)**, which is entirely focused on research methods. **PLO7 (20%)** contributes by fostering independent and creative thinking, while **PLO3 (10%)** and **PLO4 (10%)** provide the evaluative and theoretical skills necessary for effective research.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(833, 15, 2, 5, 'Self-awareness is fostered by encouraging students to reflect on their own work and the work of others. **PLO3 (20%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to critically evaluate their own work for accuracy and fairness. The other PLOs provide supporting skills for self-reflection.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(834, 15, 2, 6, 'This competency is developed through exposure to diverse audiences and communication technologies. **PLO5 (10%)**, **PLO9 (5%)**, **PLO11 (10%)**, and **PLO12 (5%)** are key, as they require students to adapt their communication styles and tools to different contexts.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(835, 15, 2, 7, 'Adaptive thinking is fostered by encouraging students to apply their knowledge to new and unfamiliar situations. **PLO11 (10%)** is central to this process, as it requires students to adapt to new tools and technologies. The other PLOs provide the foundational skills for adaptive thinking.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(836, 15, 3, 8, 'This competency is instilled by providing students with the research and analytical skills necessary for continuous learning. **PLO6 (20%)** is key, as it equips students with the ability to conduct research and evaluate information. **PLO11 (10%)** contributes by encouraging students to keep up with new technologies.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(837, 15, 3, 9, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO2 (20%)**, **PLO9 (20%)**, and **PLO12 (20%)**, which focus on understanding the history of communications, global diversity, and domestic diversity, respectively. These PLOs provide students with a broad cultural perspective.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(838, 15, 3, 10, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO5 (25%)** and **PLO3 (20%)**, which are dedicated to developing clear writing and reporting skills and the ability to evaluate communication for clarity and style. **PLO6 (10%)** and **PLO1 (10%)** provide supporting research and legal knowledge that enhances communication effectiveness.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(839, 15, 4, 11, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO9 (20%)**, and **PLO12 (20%)**, which encourage students to engage with local and international issues through the lens of media law, global diversity, and domestic diversity.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(840, 15, 4, 12, 'This competency is addressed through the program as a whole, as students are encouraged to apply their knowledge and skills within the context of Qatari and Arab society. The even distribution of weights reflects this broad-based approach.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(841, 15, 4, 13, 'This competency is strongly developed through **PLO9 (20%)** and **PLO12 (20%)**, which focus on understanding global and domestic diversity. The other PLOs contribute by providing the context for communicating with diverse audiences.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(842, 15, 4, 14, 'This competency is the primary focus of **PLO1 (30%)** and **PLO8 (20%)**, which require students to understand and apply media law and ethical frameworks. The other PLOs contribute by providing the context for ethical decision-making in mass communication.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(843, 15, 4, 15, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (30%)**, which encourages students to understand the role of the press in a free society. **PLO9 (10%)** and **PLO12 (10%)** contribute by fostering an understanding of diverse communities.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(844, 15, 5, 16, 'This competency is addressed by **PLO1 (20%)**, **PLO9 (20%)**, and **PLO12 (20%)**, which encourage students to engage with community and global issues through the lens of media law, global diversity, and domestic diversity.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(845, 15, 5, 17, 'This competency is most strongly supported by **PLO4 (20%)** and **PLO7 (20%)**, which encourage creative use of images and information and independent, creative thinking. **PLO10 (10%)** and **PLO3 (10%)** contribute by developing analytical and evaluative skills that support creative work.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(846, 15, 5, 18, 'This competency is not explicitly addressed by the program\'s PLOs, which focus primarily on individual research and analysis. However, students may develop collaborative skills through in-class activities and group projects, which are not formally assessed at the program level.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(847, 15, 5, 19, 'This competency is not a focus of the Mass Communication program. The PLOs do not address management skills, which are typically developed in business or administration programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(848, 15, 5, 20, 'While students may develop interpersonal skills through class discussions and interactions with peers and faculty, this competency is not explicitly addressed or assessed by the program\'s PLOs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14'),
(849, 15, 5, 21, 'This competency is not a focus of the Mass Communication program. The PLOs do not address leadership skills, which are typically developed through extracurricular activities or specialized leadership programs.', '', '2026-02-21 15:40:14', '2026-02-21 15:40:14');
